The defendant Eion Lee Warren was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.
  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).
  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).
  • Felon Possess Firearm, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

On the same day, at the hour of 9:59 a.m., the jury returned and by their foreperson, Anna H, brought in a verdict as follows:

"We, the jury, find the defendant, GUILTY of Possession with intent Deliver Controlled Substance, THC (200 grams or less), as charged in Count one of the Information.  Dated this 22nd day of August, 2016.  Anna H, Foreperson."
"We, the jury, find the defendant, GUILTY of Possession of a Firearm by a Felon, a .22 calibar Beretta, as charged in Count two of the Information.  Dated this 22nd day of August, 2016.  Anna H, Foreperson."
"We, the jury, find the defendant, GUILTY of Possession of a Firearm by a Felon, a FMK 9mm handgun, as charged in Count three of the Information.  Dated this 22nd day of August, 2016.  Anna H, Foreperson."
"We, the jury, find the defendant, GUILTY of Possession of a Firearm by a Felon, a 12 gauge Mossberg, as charged in Count four of the Information.  Dated this 22nd day of August, 2016.  Anna H, Foreperson."

On direction of the Court, deputy clerk polled the jury and each juror acknowledged the correctness of the verdict.  Verdict received and filed.  Court discharged the jury at 10:07 am.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.   Any issues of restitution will be determined at sentencing.   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending sentencing.   PSI ordered.
